In a refreshingly honest interview with Style magazine, Sophie, who was first discovered by fashion stylist icon Isabella Blow, also discusses her relaxed attitude to beauty and aging.

‘At the moment I don’t feel too traumatised by aging and ultimately would much rather be in my mid-thirties than my twenties, but ask me again when I’m 50,’ she says. ‘I am in slight mourning about the hollows under my eyes but that’s it. I have nothing against a good facelift.’

Sophie, the daughter of writer Tessa Dahl and granddaughter of the late children’s author Roald Dahl, became the face of Yves Saint Laurent’s perfume, Opium, in 2000.

It featured the then 22-year old naked, lying provocatively on black satin sheets with her blonde hair dyed deep red.

